How the Stanford network works: a short course in computer networking / Academic Information Resources V410.1-2 1989

Physical Description: 2 videotape(s) (vhs)

Scope and Contents

Philip Almquist, senior systems programmer at Stanford University Network introduces beginners to elementary computer networking in the first tape (80 min.). He includes the basics of TCP/IP, the design of the Stanford network, and sources for further study. The second tape (100 min.) builds on the first, discussing TCP/IP more in depth and topics relevant to host and local network administrators. Also presents an advanced discussion of the design of the Stanford network and looks at its future.
